{{Infobox university |name = Institute of Higher International Studies | native_name = ''Institut des hautes études internationales'' |image_name = Institute of Higher International Studies logo.jpg |image_size = 150px |caption = |latin_name = |motto = |established = 1921 |mottoeng = |type = |endowment = |president = |chancellor = |director =Carlo Santulli |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |staff = |faculty = |city =[[Paris]] |state = |country =[[France]] |affiliations =[[Panthéon-Assas University]] |athletics = |colors = |free_label = |free = |nickname = |website =[http://www.ihei.fr/ www.ihei.fr] |logo = |publictransit = }} The '''Institute of Higher International Studies''' ({{lang-fr|Institut des hautes études internationales}}, commonly referred to as "'''IHEI'''") is a public institution of research and higher education in [[Paris]], [[France]]. It was founded in 1921 by [[Paul Fauchille]] and [[Albert Geouffre de Lapradelle|Albert de Lapradelle]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Handbook of International Organisations|year=1927|publisher=League of Nations|page=114}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Comments Received from Governments and International Organizations and Institutions Regarding the Technical Assistance to Promote the Teaching, Study, Dissemination and Wider Appreciation of International Law|year=1963|publisher=United Nations|page=28}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Pluralism and the Idea of the Republic in France.|year=2012|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=9780230272095|page=217}}</ref> It is now affiliated to [[Panthéon-Assas University]].
